This program allows you to edit some settings of the "Server.exe"... I will explain the settings shortly, but first you have to select the "Server.exe" by clicking on the "open" button, or just type the full
path... now you're able to change the settings. By clicking on the "read settings" button you can get the current settings of the selected executable.
Server filename: This is the filename of the trojan after *installation*...Example: "Server.exe" (pleaz don't forget ".exe").
Registry key-name: This is the name that will be put in the registry to make sure the server starts every windows-boot. Can be everything... but make sure it's not too obvious like "Trojan".
Main port: This is the port to use to conect to the server...must be a number between 1 and 65535.
Keylog port: This port will be used when you activate the keylogger...must be a number between 1 and 65535, but make sure it's not the same as the main or transfer port.
Transfer port: Same as the "Keylog port", but this port is used for file-transfer.
Password: You can password protect the server to overcome connections of other "Net-Devil-users", when you connect to the server you will be promted to enter the password.

ICQ-notify: For this option you need to have icq installed (your victim not). You'll receive an icq-pager message as soon as your victim is online...The IP and port to connect to are included in the message body.
Enter your UIN (=ICQ number) and the victim's name (to keep your victim's apart).

Fake error message: If this option is enabled the server shows a fake error when the server is executed... Your victim will think: "It doesn't work...Fuck Bill Gates!!" ...ofcourse the program did his job but not what your victim expected...LOL.
